Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.35,0:16:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,different classes with other styles of demonstration. It emerges of its own. Neither I nor she calibrates
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.65,0:16:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,anything. That would be a pomposity. That would be owning yourself as the cause. It's
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.82,0:16:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,a pomposity. I think there's a you doing a that. There's neither a me nor a her. There's
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.81,0:16:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the phenomena emerging out of the propensity that in a class like this, with a subject
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.47,0:16:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,like this, those would be the conditions that would increase the likelihood of the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.23,0:17:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,emergence of intelligence. Intelligence. I believe in intelligent design. It comes to
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.36,0:17:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,certain things and then I call it stupid design. The atheists have a cop out there with intelligent
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.53,0:17:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,design and they're not taking it. They're trying to turn it down. They turn it down
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.23,0:17:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,because they think it's the leading edge of theology trying to creep into the science
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.97,0:17:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,class. I thought, here these guys have got a nice cop out. They can satisfy both sides
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.69,0:17:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,but they don't want peace. Why? Because they get too much gain from conflict. Why should
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.51,0:17:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,anybody want peace? Palestine, Israel, anything. Peace is the last thing those people want
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.31,0:17:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,because then they have to shut up and be nobody. Unless you're really retarded, you can hardly
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.79,0:17:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,fail to see the intelligence throughout the animal kingdom and evolution, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.51,0:17:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, it's the most stunning thing. Before you start worrying about being spiritual,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.69,0:18:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,start watching the Discovery Channel, the History Channel, because if you do nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.39,0:18:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,but witness deep-sea life, it's incredible ingenuity. It's incredible intelligence. It
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.83,0:18:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,makes electricity, flashes little lights, pretends to be other things. It's incredibly
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.91,0:18:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,creative. If you don't witness the progressive intelligence of life, then you shouldn't be
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.97,0:18:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,writing denunciations of anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.73,0:18:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You should go back to school. Start over. Incredible intelligence of all of life. It's
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.12,0:18:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,incredible ingenuity. Some of it comically funny. A little bobbing of a little light
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.16,0:18:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in there and 2,000 feet down there, it's got a little light bobbing like this to attract
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.64,0:18:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,people. It reads things by electricity. The shark reads you by electricity. Because every
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.18,0:18:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,time you move your muscle, you create electricity. The shark reads that. It reads things by electricity.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.58,0:18:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The shark reads you by electricity. Because every time you move your muscle, you create
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.58,0:18:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,electricity. The shark reads that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.62,0:18:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So we could use a shark for kinesiology. In other words, you understand there's many
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.39,0:19:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,ways to pick up energy fuels. I'm sure we could train a porpoise in no time to differentiate
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.39,0:19:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.19,0:19:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, next. Oh, dear heavens to me. Here I was going to tell him the secret of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.02,0:19:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew it on the way here. I can't remember what the hell it was. I had it written down
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.40,0:19:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,someplace. This is the secret of the universe. I knew it on the way here. I can't remember
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.12,0:19:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,what the hell it was. I had it written down someplace. This is the secret of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.28,0:19:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So I tried to read it out loud to feel it as intense as you can. The expression of the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.28,0:19:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,universe is where the hell's the second page?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.70,0:19:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Serenity says, at this point, do the serenity prayer. Anybody here know the serenity prayer?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.43,0:20:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,How many know the serenity prayer? Yeah. Who knows it? Can somebody say it for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.85,0:20:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Go ahead. Change the things I can. Curious to change the things I can. The wisdom, the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.53,0:20:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,own difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.77,0:20:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Grant me this right to accept the things I cannot change.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.51,0:20:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're in the middle of a disaster,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.88,0:20:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the courage is to change the things I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.54,0:20:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I can make efforts.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.18,0:20:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And the wisdom to know the difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.32,0:20:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're really praying for the capacity
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.28,0:20:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to see the difference between appearance and essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.12,0:20:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Because once I see the essence, I'm at peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.45,0:20:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,How to differentiate.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.21,0:20:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So God grant me the wisdom to discern the difference
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.19,0:20:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,between appearance and essence
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.55,0:20:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,is what that prayer is about.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.41,0:20:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, that's the great prayer of the 12-step movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.19,0:20:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And I forget the origin of that prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.93,0:20:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's used in AA all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.91,0:20:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, AA demonstrates these principles.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.79,0:21:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no such thing as a justified resentment
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.89,0:21:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,in 12-step groups.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.89,0:21:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to understand how fast people get spiritual reality?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.95,0:21:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you how fast it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.46,0:21:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,In 12-step groups, you either follow it or you die.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.90,0:21:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's amazing how fast you get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.56,0:21:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's responsible to say to a guy,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.78,0:21:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,look, you want to give up the resentment
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.46,0:21:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and you want to go out and drink it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.88,0:21:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You got your choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.46,0:21:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to forgive the guy or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.02,0:21:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not giving him a son of a bitch.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.60,0:21:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't deserve it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.20,0:21:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So the basic principle, there are no justified resentments.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.42,0:21:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, you got to be willing to surrender
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.14,0:21:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the juice you're getting out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.40,0:21:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So the first principle in 12-step groups
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.10,0:21:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,is to surrender your life to God as you understand him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.36,0:21:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrender your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.42,0:21:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You have a higher power as you understand him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.92,0:21:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And then out of that humility,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.98,0:21:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you're willing to surrender the juice
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.52,0:21:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you're getting out of the resentment.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.89,0:21:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, they have a gun to their head.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.88,0:22:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, you die.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.78,0:22:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Resentments kill more recovering alcoholics
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.19,0:22:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,than anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.29,0:22:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Resentments kill more recovering alkies
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.53,0:22:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,than anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.97,0:22:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You got your choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.19,0:22:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrender it to God or croak.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.95,0:22:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's a slow death, slow death.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.19,0:22:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.84,0:22:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We've covered sort of some of the basics
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.32,0:22:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,which may have sounded a little bit off
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.06,0:22:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,from what we were usually talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.64,0:22:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But I think you have to stay current
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.04,0:22:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,with what's happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.10,0:22:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And I also want to demonstrate.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.36,0:22:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Spirituality means to stand up for truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.40,0:22:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't mean to passively lie down
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.42,0:22:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and allow yourself to become a victim
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.12,0:22:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and think that you're being pious and holy with all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.45,0:22:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Piety and holiness means also to stand for the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.63,0:22:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And because truth is also strength,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.17,0:22:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,strength and commitment.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.80,0:22:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'm going to start with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.82,0:22:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'm going to start with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.88,0:22:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'm going to start with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.94,0:22:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'm going to start with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.00,0:22:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'm going to start with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.06,0:22:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'm going to start with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.18,0:22:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when you commit to the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.66,0:22:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,then you stand for the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.35,0:22:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's up to your wisdom how and when to express it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.35,0:23:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But nevertheless, we stand for that which we believe in.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.75,0:23:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, we are people without principles.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.63,0:23:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Without principles, one is weak and an easy knockover.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.63,0:23:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the value of mores and principles,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.35,0:23:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual principles, religious principles,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.93,0:23:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,logic, reason, is it gives you strength to your character.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.99,0:23:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And in times of great stress, that's when you're going to need that character.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.44,0:23:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,When you need it, it's there because it's habitual, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.62,0:23:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, some people grew up in very fortunate environments
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.78,0:23:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,where commitment to the truth is a very strong principle.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.96,0:23:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,In the world I grew up in, lying was probably the worst of all.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.62,0:23:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody thought of murder or anything like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.58,0:23:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the ordinary person, lying was the most grievous thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.63,0:23:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd rather die than lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.51,0:24:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, it would put a spot on your soul that God could see.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.01,0:24:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, spots on your soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.67,0:24:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So, anyway, the world I grew up in, as I say, was somewhat politicized.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.05,0:24:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.77,0:24:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I grew up with a respect for truth and alignment with truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.91,0:24:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is the basis of integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.71,0:24:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.64,0:24:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Serenity comes out of the certainty that you come.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.06,0:24:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a certainty that comes from the knowingness of your alignment
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.14,0:24:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and the absoluteness of that alignment.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.00,0:24:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That gives you a strength and a power and a courage to stand up against anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.88,0:24:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And with that, you can walk into the bullets.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.30,0:24:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you walk into the bullets, you go all the way to the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.60,0:24:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So, now we will reconvene at what time?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.12,0:24:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Two, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.32,0:24:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.02,0:25:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, we're all assembled.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.28,0:25:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to start.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.58,0:25:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This year, we gave monthly lectures, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.36,0:25:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Next year, we thought we'd cut it down to half a day every other month.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.49,0:25:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're going to devote it primarily just to discussion, question and answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.14,0:25:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We presented all the didactic material.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.14,0:25:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll probably start it with, you know, commentary on what's current or coming up or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.56,0:25:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But I thought we're going to spend more traditional, what do they call it, satsang, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.46,0:25:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Where you sit with the group.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.60,0:25:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And you discuss questions and answers.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.52,0:25:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And I liked it when we wandered through the audience and chatted with people more or less informally.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.30,0:25:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But that depends on whether Robert can work it out or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.38,0:25:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So, does that meet with approval?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.37,0:26:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what you get for asking a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.49,0:26:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we'll see what we can do about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.52,0:26:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We thought we'd leave it up to the group.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.10,0:26:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But I thought we want to spend more time with spontaneous, spontaneous clarification, spontaneous question and answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.33,0:26:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, personal response, you know, you're stuck in this and how do I get off of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.85,0:26:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not seeing something.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.85,0:26:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we work together, sort of.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.49,0:26:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I've done that, it's been sort of fun, you know, sort of more informal.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.87,0:26:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And less didactic.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.65,0:26:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But I leave it up to everybody, you know, the vote.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.37,0:26:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I go with the vote, however it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.19,0:26:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll email you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.87,0:26:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.69,0:26:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.23,0:26:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll email you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.81,0:26:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.33,0:27:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll email you.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.63,0:27:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.03,0:27:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Put it on your blog site.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.64,0:27:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Blog.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.87,0:27:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Got to be said correctly.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.35,0:27:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Blog site.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.04,0:27:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I've got a blog site.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.42,0:27:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, big time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.09,0:27:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.49,0:27:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's return to the activity of the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.94,0:27:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.48,0:27:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that where we ended?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.74,0:27:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't remember if we ended there.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.04,0:27:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we wanted to do, we did brain function, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.14,0:27:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Did we do consciousness and rate of...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.51,0:27:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Did we do consciousness and rate of happiness?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.84,0:27:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know where we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.76,0:28:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, we did brain function.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.36,0:28:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.08,0:28:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll do societal problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.08,0:28:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I think we'll...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.22,0:28:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we'll skip the maps of the world, and we'll skip to 33, consciousness and rate of happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.78,0:28:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.08,0:28:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,23, 24, then we'll skip to 33.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.84,0:28:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.92,0:28:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We intend to put all the charts together from all the lectures and all the books and put it together and make it available in sort of an oversized books.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.56,0:28:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, a lot of people like the charts.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.00,0:28:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'd have a chart on this side and an explanation on this side, which would be sort of...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.46,0:28:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's hard to see everything on the board and comprehend it, and to have it all together would be sort of fun, nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.97,0:28:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.25,0:28:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is just to reflect that happiness is an intrinsic quality, not dependent on anything out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.14,0:29:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see the level of consciousness, and we correlate this with social problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.74,0:29:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, happiness is another chart.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.08,0:29:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We correlate this...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.96,0:29:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We correlate this with social problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.14,0:29:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the rate of unemployment at the bottom here.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.64,0:29:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,50 is usually the federal prison population.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.56,0:29:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Unemployment is 97%.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.44,0:29:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Rate of poverty is 65%.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.94,0:29:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because they're good thieves.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.94,0:29:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, it would be...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.12,0:29:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Rate of happiness, however, is zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.09,0:29:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.63,0:29:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Rate of criminality, 98%.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.79,0:29:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It's pretty much a criminal level of mentality.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.05,0:29:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Where you shoot at the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.13,0:29:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,People coming to rescue you, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.93,0:29:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's a helicopter coming to rescue you, and you shoot at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.93,0:29:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.09,0:29:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.94,0:29:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Rate of unemployment, as you go higher, is still 75%.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.11,0:30:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Poverty is 40%.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.35,0:30:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness is 2%.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.87,0:30:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Rate of criminality drops from 98% to 91%.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.97,0:30:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,91%.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.91,0:30:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, 100 to 200, you see the rate of unemployment is still 50%.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.71,0:30:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, you see the rate of unemployment is still 50%.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.69,0:30:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Poverty is about a quarter.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.24,0:30:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness is still relatively rare, only 15%.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.28,0:30:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And 50% are still into criminality.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.48,0:30:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,If the cop is not looking, they'll cop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.26,0:30:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.77,0:30:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, 200 to 300, you're coming up...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.47,0:30:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The rate of unemployment suddenly drops to only 8%.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.49,0:30:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You know?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.07,0:30:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.91,0:30:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this is a big jump right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.39,0:30:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's because you went over 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.19,0:30:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, there should be a line here denoting.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.14,0:30:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So, below 200, unemployment is 50%.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.06,0:30:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 200, unemployment is only 8%.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.88,0:30:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So, again, you see 200 is the level that demarcates a profound difference
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.60,0:31:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,in brain physiology, brain psychology, happiness, employment, criminality.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.64,0:31:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Very critical level.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.94,0:31:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,200 to 300, unemployment is only 8% now.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.20,0:31:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Poverty is down to 1.5%.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.44,0:31:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness, at least 40% of people think they're happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.33,0:31:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And criminality drops to 99%, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.09,0:31:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we're here, we get to the 300s, which is good natured enthusiasm, and unemployment
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.40,0:31:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is 7%.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.40,0:31:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And they're probably on unemployment checks.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.26,0:31:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Rate of poverty is only 1%.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.56,0:31:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness, at least 50% are happy already.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.76,0:31:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And only 5% are still into criminality.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.94,0:31:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.94,0:31:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We hit the level of the intellect, the 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.58,0:31:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the level of science, medicine, technology, college education.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.68,0:31:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,2% unemployment.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.32,0:32:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Poverty, 0.5, very rare.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.30,0:32:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness, the majority, 70%.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.50,0:32:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Criminality drops to 2%.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.54,0:32:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what they're up to.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.08,0:32:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I should get some of these folks in.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.84,0:32:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you up to?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.40,0:32:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe that's Enron or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.94,0:32:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what the 2% is doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.48,0:32:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess caught up in greed, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.87,0:32:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Then at 500, you see, this is the linear domain of the, the linear domain.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.52,0:32:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This is where we shift brain physiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.66,0:32:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And now we, now the basic reality is non-linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.12,0:32:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,500 and up is the energy field of love and the spiritual reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.90,0:32:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the rate of unemployment is 0%, 0, 0.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.12,0:32:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The rate of poverty, 0.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.05,0:32:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness, 98%.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.05,0:32:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,0.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.34,0:32:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,0.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.34,0:32:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,98%.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.06,0:32:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Criminality, 0.5.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.72,0:32:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know who they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.72,0:32:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.72,0:32:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So, then at 600, you see, these are all 0.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.04,0:32:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness is, of course, 100%.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.04,0:33:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And criminality is not even a thinkable option, not even thinkable.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.64,0:33:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need laws to control people because they wouldn't even think of it in the first
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.31,0:33:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,place.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.31,0:33:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, to kill somebody for their money wouldn't even be, you know, kind of a thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.03,0:33:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,an option.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.03,0:33:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Move to the next, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.19,0:33:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see the necessity for law from 200 down because you see what happens with anarchy.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.16,0:33:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Chomsky's, Chomsky, Noam Chomsky is an anarchist, you know, atheist anarchist.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.48,0:33:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have here a Chomsky demonstration of anarchy.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.04,0:33:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,How anybody could rationalize that?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.80,0:33:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.80,0:33:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You could rationally choose anarchy, we have it in the Gulf Coast right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.36,0:34:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what anarchy looks like, is the people at the bottom are let loose, predatory.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.34,0:34:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So anarchy is really not Shangri-La.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.99,0:34:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody wrote me, how come I didn't lump Chomsky in with the Dalai Lama?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.06,0:34:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Because he's for peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.40,0:34:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.87,0:34:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.87,0:34:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway, an atheist, all right, rate of happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.09,0:34:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So here we have it again, no, the other way, yes, here we have it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.27,0:34:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,At these various levels, you see, guilt, it blocked 30, four, only 4%, probably because
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.46,0:35:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,they're in denial or something, and so you see the correlation is not with wealth, fame,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.94,0:35:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,any worldly gain.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.94,0:35:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Good looks, it's about 100% aligned completely with level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.14,0:35:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,See because relativism or social relativism is that there's something out there causing
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.28,0:35:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,a this, and as we see from the calibrated levels of consciousness, there's no is that
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.02,0:35:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,causing a this.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.84,0:35:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,There's this being what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.04,0:35:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.04,0:35:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It acts to itself as a consequence of that which it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.67,0:35:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So projecting causality externally, of course, is the difficulty with Marxism, a perpetrator
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.47,0:35:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,victim than the evil capitalist, et cetera, and the evil government, the evil law, the
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.85,0:35:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,evil law and order.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.85,0:35:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But we see what happens when you remove it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.85,0:36:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens when you remove those things is pathetic indeed, they're pathetic indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.36,0:36:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Pathetic indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.36,0:36:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They shoot down.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.36,0:36:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The rebel government is coming to rescue them.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.58,0:36:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.92,0:36:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.92,0:36:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So much for anarchy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.60,0:36:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody here still an enthusiast for anarchy, a Chomsky fan?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.46,0:36:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to offend any Chomsky fans, but they should leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.76,0:36:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The audience, immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.84,0:36:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.70,0:36:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So why do people get stuck in these positionalities?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.66,0:36:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,This is generally the dualities of attraction and aversion.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.48,0:36:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,To be, to, nonattachment.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.74,0:36:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Attachment means to let go all attachments, all attractions, and all aversions.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.36,0:36:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You're neither attracted to it, nor do you have an aversion to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.09,0:36:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, if you die, you die.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.59,0:36:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you're not attracted to it, neither do you resist it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.65,0:36:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever will be, will be.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.49,0:36:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the Beatles had a song, Let It Be, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.65,0:37:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Let It Be.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.35,0:37:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I calibrated that once.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.64,0:37:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It was very high, I forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.73,0:37:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The stones responded to that with Let It Bleed.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.02,0:37:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,People ask me, because the stones, I calibrated at different levels in different places.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.40,0:37:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I was at Woodstock, you know, and it was, yeah, I was at Woodstock.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.69,0:37:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,All the mud and the rain, and the only food got in was a big trickle watermelon.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.13,0:37:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And there was the LSD Rescue Squad.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.07,0:37:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was a member of the LSD Rescue Squad.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.23,0:37:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So, somebody freaked out.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.65,0:37:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We talked them down and stuffed them with vitamin B3 to try and offset it, you know, rather than tranquilizers, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.99,0:37:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And the only person I really saw very upset was the old lady who lived there.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.45,0:38:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I got there.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.87,0:38:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Frank Yeager's farm, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.01,0:38:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And I got there a day early and parked across the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.51,0:38:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And the next morning, we got up.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.17,0:38:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The trees were full of people, hippies.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.45,0:38:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And all of a sudden, I got up.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.41,0:38:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,All over her porch, there were hippies on the ground, hippies hanging in the trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.50,0:38:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Tied blankets from one branch to another, and there was a hippie.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.19,0:38:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I was rescuing people.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.83,0:38:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the lady panicked.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.20,0:38:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I went over to talk to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.56,0:38:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And I told her, these were peace people.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.00,0:38:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's peaceniks.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.38,0:38:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The weekend was love, music, and peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.46,0:38:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that wouldn't attract 450,000 people.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.76,0:38:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what would.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.40,0:38:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Plus, whoever, you know, the bands they had.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.74,0:38:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.12,0:38:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I told the lady, these are, they're all here for peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.52,0:38:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all for peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.90,0:38:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And she felt a little better.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.10,0:38:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I had to reassure her a couple of times over the weekend.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.82,0:38:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But I was the only one that had fresh water.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.96,0:39:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,She gave me water in return.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.32,0:39:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody else drank water that had so much chlorine in it, it would really gag you.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.98,0:39:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it was chlorine.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.00,0:39:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought, well, I'll go back to Max Yeager's farm next year.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.34,0:39:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's going to be watermelons for miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.96,0:39:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Watermelons for miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.12,0:39:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Watermelon seeds everywhere to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.45,0:39:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, after that Altamont, there was the East Village Other.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.23,0:39:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It was an avant-garde newspaper, a great paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.12,0:39:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,East Village Other had great art in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.38,0:39:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was very intuitive.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.16,0:39:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What the East Village Other talked about would surface in society a couple of months later.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.18,0:39:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like song lyrics will pick up a trend before it surfaces in the daily news, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.81,0:39:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And I remember the advertisement.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.99,0:39:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,They advertised Altamont, and around the advertising were bullets.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.43,0:39:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.92,0:40:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in the early days, the Fillmore East or something, people smoked grass, and they'd sit around and went home, and were very peaceful.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.50,0:40:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, slowly, we saw a change.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.84,0:40:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,People began to get drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.18,0:40:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And alcohol is a whole different energy than smoking pot.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.02,0:40:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's impossible to get violent on pot, but it's easy to get violent on alcohol.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.90,0:40:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when I saw Altamont, the bullets, plus the appearance now of Altamont,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.02,0:40:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and the appearance now of alcohol at rock concerts, I said, I don't think I'm going to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.22,0:40:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't go.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.94,0:40:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, that's where he sang Sympathy for the Devil, and they murdered the motorcycle guys who were protective at Woodstock,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.84,0:40:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and now killed the guy right in front of the stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.48,0:40:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So, at that time, the Stones, Let It Bleed, Sympathy for the Devil, and Murder, you know, their energy was down.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.08,0:40:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And I forget what it calibrated, blow 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.90,0:40:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, they came out of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.26,0:40:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.90,0:40:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.26,0:40:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We're in the 300s, because they've got a great rapport with their audience, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.26,0:41:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And the group hung together with a group commitment to each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.34,0:41:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The Beatles all went off on their own hook, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.20,0:41:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,They were more intellectual, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.91,0:41:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But the Stones hung out as a group.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.09,0:41:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I think the Stones more currently calibrated over 300 or 350 or something, which is enthusiasm.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.89,0:41:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And they sure got a lot of enthusiasm, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.09,0:41:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So, a thing may calibrate differently depending on difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.33,0:41:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.33,0:41:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're worshiping the devil and getting murdered in front of the, while the music
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.90,0:41:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,goes on, that's going to sort of bring your calibration down a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.82,0:41:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Let It Be is surrendering it to God, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.28,0:41:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's pretty much like the first step in the 12-step groups.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.40,0:41:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Let It Be means to surrender to as it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.26,0:41:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.26,0:41:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.26,0:41:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.33,0:41:52.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.33,0:41:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it keeps the attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.74,0:41:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.54,0:41:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the attractions and the aversions going then.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.44,0:42:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,This experiencer cutting edge of the ego, which is our inheritance from the animal evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.76,0:42:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,of life on this planet, essential to life, but no longer necessary, and a deterrent to
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.94,0:42:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.80,0:42:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But what keeps us stuck then in the domain of the ego, which spiritual people struggle
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.32,0:42:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,with to overcome?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.96,0:42:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, the one attraction is we cling to it because it's easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.60,0:42:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's familiar.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.78,0:42:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And you've got to change, and change is going to take effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.06,0:42:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So you decide, I'm not going to curse anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.52,0:42:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to curse anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.82,0:42:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But you've got to remember that takes effort, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.44,0:42:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to try to be kindly instead of greedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.94,0:42:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, getting the best of the deal gets to be a habit.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.08,0:42:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,There's certain cultures, especially in New York, where if you don't get the best of the
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.22,0:42:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,deal, you're ashamed to come home.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.80,0:42:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.70,0:42:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Even Steven means you just lost out, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.24,0:43:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I gave him a fair deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.48,0:43:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's the best you could do?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.30,0:43:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So we cling to the familiar.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.12,0:43:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see that.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.12,0:43:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, it's easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.52,0:43:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't take effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.22,0:43:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, we have pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.32,0:43:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody secretly thinks that their view of the world is correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.50,0:43:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And to change would require humility.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.10,0:43:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Humility is a challenge to the narcissistic core of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.42,0:43:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The last thing we need to do is to change.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.42,0:43:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Humility is a challenge to the narcissistic core of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.42,0:43:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The last thing we need to do is to change.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.34,0:43:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The last thing the ego wants to hear about is humility.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.01,0:43:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And it, because it holds its position, the narcissistic ego is subject to humiliation.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.87,0:43:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So the ego confuses humility and humiliation.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.54,0:43:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is humble is immune to humiliation.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.66,0:43:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm fat, ugly, and stupid, so?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.26,0:43:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And a bullhunk besides.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.26,0:43:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What can you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.26,0:43:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And I flunked out of grade school.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.30,0:43:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.30,0:43:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.30,0:44:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.30,0:44:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I flunked out of grade school.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.98,0:44:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm lazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.98,0:44:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I sure am, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.98,0:44:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't move unless I got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.98,0:44:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, what can you say to a guy like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.57,0:44:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.57,0:44:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.86,0:44:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And as I noted, the black comedians, my favorite was the guy who...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.86,0:44:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Richard Pryor.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.62,0:44:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.62,0:44:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Pryor, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.62,0:44:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I've mentioned him before.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.72,0:44:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, he took the wind out of anti-colored prejudice.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.26,0:44:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,He just took the wind out of it, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.94,0:44:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, what could you say after what he said about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.94,0:44:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He just took the stereotype.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.82,0:44:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you know, turned it into shreds.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.90,0:44:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You felt like an idiot, you know, jumping for an old stereotype when he just destroyed
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.06,0:44:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,it altogether.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.50,0:44:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you accept about yourself makes you immune.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.35,0:44:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you're sensitive or your feelings get hurt, you sit down and write out all the worst
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.79,0:44:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,things you can think about yourself and own it and feel that that's just fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.89,0:45:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you feel it's just fine, then you stop worrying about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.48,0:45:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So letting go of pride, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.72,0:45:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Anger, the confusion of anger with strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.82,0:45:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,See the animal puffs up with anger, the gorilla pounces his thing, birds swell, to try and
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.78,0:45:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,intimidate, which works in the jungle.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.64,0:45:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.64,0:45:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The mouse meets the elephant and the elephant challenges the elephant.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.41,0:45:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And the elephant says, I'm the king of the jungle and I challenge you to a fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.49,0:45:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And the mouse says, well, I'd like to.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.05,0:45:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But I've been sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.05,0:45:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So you puff up with anger and that's the illusion of strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.29,0:45:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What is strength?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.29,0:46:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Strength is standing for truth when confronted with adversity.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.88,0:46:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's standing for integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.10,0:46:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You stand for the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.48,0:46:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You stand for the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.32,0:46:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't run from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.32,0:46:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither do you challenge it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.64,0:46:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither do you swell up.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.64,0:46:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You just say, that's the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.56,0:46:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, you are dead wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.14,0:46:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.08,0:46:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So the ego, of course, always wants to win and has an aversion to losing.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.47,0:46:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And here you have the narcissistic ego of the blogger because he wants to be somebody
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.43,0:46:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and not...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.43,0:46:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And he dreads being nobody.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.34,0:46:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's better to be somebody than to be nobody.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.46,0:46:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So people will go to any extreme to be somebody.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.28,0:46:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,They shot John Lennon, the guy who shot John Lennon.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.10,0:46:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,His only motivation was envy and he wanted to be somebody.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.86,0:47:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, he didn't shoot the guy just so you can be somebody.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.46,0:47:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,To be somebody, he shot Lennon dead in the west side of New York City in the very famous
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.86,0:47:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,apartment building.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.86,0:47:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget the name of the...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.54,0:47:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, the Dakota, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.54,0:47:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Dakota is a very famous apartment building, west side of the park, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.92,0:47:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And I used to...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.92,0:47:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,There's twin towers.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.92,0:47:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The other tower was a psychoanalyst who was a supervising analyst of mine from Mount Sinai.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.38,0:47:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And I went to a meeting or a party there with him one evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.46,0:47:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's the two towers.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.06,0:47:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got this one at the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.70,0:47:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Twin towers, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.70,0:47:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So the penthouse, you could walk out on this terrace.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.08,0:47:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And the terrace had a wall, brick wall, so the wall was only this wide and went around
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.82,0:47:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.82,0:47:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It was only about this high.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.82,0:48:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I should give you, freaks, just looking down, 62 stories or whatever it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.96,0:48:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And his cat would walk around this parapet.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.04,0:48:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't even watch him.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.68,0:48:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't even watch him.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.00,0:48:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, oh, he knows where he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.24,0:48:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure-footed cat walking around.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.24,0:48:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Very funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.40,0:48:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.40,0:48:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.40,0:48:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So importance, people are willing to do anything, even kill a celebrity and thereby gain notoriety.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.96,0:48:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, gain and loss is so obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.20,0:48:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Money of course becomes an addiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.07,0:48:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The addiction to money, some people have so much money they don't know what to do with
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.67,0:48:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.74,0:48:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And the addiction to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.74,0:48:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Back east, I knew all the people who were there.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.06,0:48:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Great.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.06,0:48:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,They had the greatest money.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.06,0:48:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,They had the greatest fortunes.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.30,0:48:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all third and fourth generation.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.06,0:48:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And very exclusive enclave.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.06,0:49:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The world doesn't even know about them.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.06,0:49:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, they were all, what do you call it, babies and?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.06,0:49:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.50,0:49:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Just one baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.08,0:49:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Just one baby, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.08,0:49:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And lived in big estates, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.08,0:49:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I would visit them, big 50-roomed little Georgians and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.32,0:49:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And a lot of them, as they got older, would have a little apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.08,0:49:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,They'd have the kitchen and a bedroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.08,0:49:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And a little sitting room.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.08,0:49:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,They'd be these three little rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.08,0:49:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's this huge estate covering many acres.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.08,0:49:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And they lived in these three rooms for years.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.08,0:49:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'd say, what's in that building.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.08,0:49:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,They'd say, Jesus, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.08,0:49:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't been there in 10 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.08,0:49:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't been there in 10 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.08,0:49:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,A friend of mine lived in a big Georgian down on, on the, on Mill River Road in Upper
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.78,0:49:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Vokeville.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.78,0:49:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And she lived in a huge Georgian, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.78,0:49:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,again, came into money, and I was asking, I was visiting her one time, and I said, what's
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.22,0:49:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that? And she said, well, that's the dining room. And I said, what's on that? And she
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.44,0:50:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,says, I don't know. I've never been past the dining room. That was the kitchen, the
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.28,0:50:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,servants' quarters, the whole big, huge wing of this giant Georgian house. She says, I
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.16,0:50:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,don't know. I've never been past the dining room. That's funny. Okay. So she just took
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.40,0:50:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,money for granted. All right. So we desire, the ego keeps desiring excitement. This is
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.08,0:50:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the excitement of thinkingness. The experiencer is out there using every thought and passing
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.06,0:50:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,opinion. The ego, of course, is run by wantingness and has a fear that it won't get. It loves
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.98,0:50:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,status and hates being a nobody. It wants to be noticed and hates the idea of being
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.08,0:50:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,ignored. It wants to express its opinion. It loves the soapbox and doesn't want to just
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.24,0:50:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,shut up.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.42,0:50:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up and be ordinary. It craves and it dreads. So it controls to save the world instead
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.60,0:51:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,of surrendering it. It likes novelty. It hates boredom. It likes thrill. It's afraid it might
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.46,0:51:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,miss out. It's very aggressive and is afraid of being passive. Wants to be the in-group.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.19,0:51:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Wants to be elite. Correct. Politically correct. Wants to be in the in-group. Wants to be fashionable.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.84,0:51:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Picks up the latest meme.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.64,0:51:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever the punch word is in order to show that they're very hip. They want to be fashionable.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.86,0:51:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,They want to be right. Superior. The funniest thing about elitism is that what they're elite
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.08,0:51:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,about is their egalitarianism. What makes them superior is that they are politically
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.49,0:51:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,for egalitarianism, which means that everybody is equal.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.83,0:52:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you're the champion of equality, this makes you superior. You get the inference, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.32,0:52:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So superior. It wants to speak up rather than to shut up. It's stubborn.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.82,0:52:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Would rather die than give in. Wants to be famous rather than anonymous.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.71,0:52:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as you see a terrorist incident, you see the groups rushing to claim credit. Claim credit.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.85,0:52:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd think they'd want to escape in the other direction, not be known who blew it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.70,0:52:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But you see the groups rushing to claim fame for blowing up a busload of kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.42,0:52:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So the attraction is to resist, to defend, to be special, to be more, to own things.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.99,0:52:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we have the magicalness of owning, which is a whole lecture in itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.90,0:53:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, there is, you know, in reality, there is no such thing as owning.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.96,0:53:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not possible to own anything. First of all, everything belongs to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.12,0:53:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You have temporary stewardship. You have the right of control by legal agreement.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.68,0:53:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can't own anything. How could you own it?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.81,0:53:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You would have to be like an octopus and suck it into yourself so that it becomes you, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.63,0:53:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But once you've done that, you've destroyed it so you can't own it anymore because you just ate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.97,0:53:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so the thought of own gives everything a specialness, a uniqueness.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.93,0:53:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, that's why my, the word my, is so magical.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.42,0:53:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, that's just a watch. That's just a watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.51,0:53:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Not the minute I own it, it's my watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.34,0:54:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it's very special. Now it's my favorite watch. Good God.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.82,0:54:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You see what happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.34,0:54:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The illusion of owning, then, is a mentalization.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.78,0:54:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't own anything. You can use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.41,0:54:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You have temporary stewardship of it, even this body.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.15,0:54:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Do I own it? I don't own it. It just is there.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.96,0:54:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,At age three, I discovered the rotten thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.34,0:54:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I was perfectly happy in oblivion.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.25,0:54:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,All of a sudden, smash-o. The light goes on.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.61,0:54:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And I realize I exist. God, my.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.77,0:54:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as the realization of existence came up out of nothingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.49,0:54:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,immediately arose the fear of nonexistence.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.04,0:54:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,If you exist, you see, then the fear is you will not exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.56,0:54:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Immediately, the fear of death arises.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.18,0:55:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And to make matters worse, there was this little body, the roll call me, in this wagon.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.17,0:55:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only do you exist, therefore, you have to face the terror of nonexistence.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.35,0:55:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But a body went with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.35,0:55:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's taken me 75 years to recover from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.32,0:55:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.32,0:55:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So you own. And that, of course, has to do with control.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.90,0:55:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather than realize the reality is that of stewardship.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.90,0:55:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything belongs to God. Nothing belongs to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.90,0:55:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you leave here, you're going to take nothing with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.90,0:55:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The body arose from the dust, and it returns to the dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.32,0:55:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not going to take it with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.32,0:55:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what can you take with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.32,0:55:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You can only take with you what you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.32,0:55:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.35,0:55:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What you have become is the transcendent reality
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.35,0:55:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that leaves the body and then is in a more familiar domain.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.53,0:56:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,As people go out of the body, you know, out-of-body experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.53,0:56:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,as we said before, their calibration doesn't change.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.53,0:56:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason is they know it all along. They know it all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.53,0:56:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute you come into a body, you forget that.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.53,0:56:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute you go out-of-body, that is your natural state.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.53,0:56:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That's your natural state.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.53,0:56:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you know it all the time and just, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.69,0:56:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,repress it when you're in a physical body,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.69,0:56:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,your consciousness doesn't go up.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.69,0:56:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Out-of-body consciousness remains the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.69,0:56:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Near-death experience, that's something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.69,0:56:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Near-death experience is transformative.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.69,0:56:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The infinite presence is so exquisite
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.72,0:56:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that, ah,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.20,0:56:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,ah,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.20,0:56:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,one is never the same again.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.20,0:56:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so we move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.96,0:56:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so that's the illusion of ownership.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.96,0:56:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we have a trait. You want to be unique.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.96,0:56:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,People want to change the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.96,0:56:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They change it, they mean they want to change it
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.96,0:57:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to what they want it to become.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.96,0:57:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They change the world so it conforms with their idea of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.96,0:57:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And to do that, they'll work with facts and lie and steal.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.96,0:57:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, this one, the attraction is to condemn people.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.12,0:57:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The aversion is to forgive them.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.12,0:57:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,As I was saying, World War II is over 60 years
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.12,0:57:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet here's this guy on TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.12,0:57:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,He's just, he ain't going to forgive them.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.12,0:57:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they don't deserve it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.12,0:57:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So his illusion is if he forgives, the other person has a gain.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.12,0:57:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But he doesn't realize that the one who gains by the forgiveness is him.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.19,0:57:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He's the one that gains by the forgiveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.19,0:57:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But he doesn't want to give the gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.19,0:57:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He sees it as giving away a gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.19,0:57:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you see the difficulty of forgiveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.24,0:57:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The difficulty of the narcissistic ways of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.24,0:57:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The current, what I can see, sort of the decline.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.40,0:57:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Trying to blame responsibility out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.40,0:57:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, condemn, blame.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.50,0:58:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And instead of owning responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.63,0:58:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,This wants to hold on to everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.63,0:58:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Has an aversion to letting go.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.92,0:58:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And the ego wants to dominate.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.72,0:58:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It is aligned with the content.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.72,0:58:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Whereas reality, what it doesn't want to do is surrender it.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.72,0:58:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So, God grant me the serenity to accept the things I cannot change.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.88,0:58:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And turn it over to God is just what the ego doesn't want to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.07,0:58:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It wants to dominate and hold on to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.07,0:58:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's aligned with the content.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.29,0:58:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,When you turn it over to God, you're surrendering it to the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.29,0:58:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is the same as the course of miracles.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.29,0:58:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,When you ask the Holy Spirit for a miracle, you're asking to see it differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.29,0:58:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You're asking the Holy Spirit to transcend your fixation on the linear to see the non-linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.39,0:58:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And within the non-linear, you see that it's all perfectly fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.39,0:58:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.71,0:59:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this is involved with dominating the content.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.71,0:59:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It wants abundance rather than frugality.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.19,0:59:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't like frugality.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.25,0:59:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It would prefer to be a martyr rather than just accepting.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.25,0:59:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It has attracted to being the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.44,0:59:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the value.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.44,0:59:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,This is moral relativism and social relativism.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.44,0:59:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,In which everybody is the victim of something out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.44,0:59:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody is the victim of something out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.80,0:59:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Just victimization itself is a contextualization, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.69,0:59:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The wind comes and things are knocked over.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.98,0:59:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But to see yourself as a victim,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.20,0:59:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,is different than seeing yourself as the participant.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.68,0:59:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a participant.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.68,0:59:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not the victim of it, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.68,0:59:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a participant.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.81,0:59:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And surrendering it to God does bring the miraculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.81,1:00:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,When I first came to Arizona, I got it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.97,1:00:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I still have a 64 Willis three-quarter ton pickup truck.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.04,1:00:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was my only vehicle.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.04,1:00:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So I left the East.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.04,1:00:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I threw my tools in the back.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.04,1:00:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I said goodbye to everything and walked away.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.04,1:00:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Drove out here.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.04,1:00:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And there I am on the southern border.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.04,1:00:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,North of Mexico.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.04,1:00:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And I still didn't have any idea of distance.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.04,1:00:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I had no idea how, you know, the great distance in the West.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.04,1:00:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm in this little truck by myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.04,1:00:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And I really don't have any water or anything, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.04,1:00:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm exploring out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.04,1:00:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought, well, in another few miles I'll come to a town.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.04,1:00:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I drove for an hour.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.04,1:00:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,There was never any town.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.04,1:00:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Drove for another hour.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.04,1:00:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,There's still no town.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.04,1:00:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You can drive for hours down there and see no town.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.04,1:00:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally I parked.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.20,1:00:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And the truck went on fire.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.20,1:00:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So I got no water.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.09,1:00:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm dehydrated.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.09,1:00:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm exhausted.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.09,1:00:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And the truck is on fire.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.09,1:00:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And inside the cab, the smoke is shooting.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.09,1:01:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't see.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.09,1:01:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way you can see where the fire is coming from.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.09,1:01:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And I had heat exhaustion.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.32,1:01:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So I knew I couldn't walk 20 feet from the truck, much less walk to the nearest town or water, seeing as I had already driven an hour and didn't see any anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.32,1:01:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So I just got ready to go.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.35,1:01:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So I just got ready to die.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.35,1:01:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought, oh, great.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.35,1:01:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll leave.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.35,1:01:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.35,1:01:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So I sit there waiting to leave.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.66,1:01:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I've done it a number of times.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.66,1:01:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, your death is a certainty.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.66,1:01:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And so you say, okay, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.66,1:01:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So next thing I know, annoyingness, I've never heard any other.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.68,1:01:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never in all my spiritual experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.68,1:01:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,There's never been an other, you know, like a voice or a vision or a spirit teacher or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.61,1:01:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But from within came an annoyingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.03,1:01:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And the annoyingness was, take the screwdriver.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.03,1:01:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a glove compartment.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.03,1:01:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But the front was old and fell off.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.03,1:02:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So here was just these tools.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.03,1:02:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You may not realize it, but a glove compartment is just lined with cardboard.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.03,1:02:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You think that's steel in there or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.03,1:02:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just cardboard.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.19,1:02:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So the annoyingness was to take the screwdriver and jam it through the bottom of the glove compartment.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.25,1:02:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So I did.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.25,1:02:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.25,1:02:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the annoyingness came.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.25,1:02:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,There was about this much coffee in the bottom of a Styrofoam cup.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.25,1:02:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Poured through the hole.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.96,1:02:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm not going to resist it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.96,1:02:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I poured it through the hole.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.76,1:02:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Kissed the one out.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.76,1:02:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Good God.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.76,1:02:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The fire was an electrical fire from the cigarette lighter.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.76,1:02:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was the exact locus of the fire, which would not be knowable via left brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.76,1:02:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Plus the electrical harness of that old truck has been redone about 80 times.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.76,1:02:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And it looks like a crazy snarl.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.76,1:02:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd never figure it out.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.76,1:02:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't have the energy to lift the hood, much less do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.76,1:02:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So out of the annoyingness came to pour that in there.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.76,1:03:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So life went on.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.88,1:03:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,A little disappointed, but so be it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.08,1:03:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The annoyingness that arises from within.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.72,1:03:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.72,1:03:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened to our projectionist?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.68,1:03:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.28,1:03:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.28,1:03:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So letting go of control then, letting go of wanting to control, or even to survive,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.28,1:03:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,opened the door to annoyingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.69,1:03:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So I did not see myself as the victim of drought and all those things.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.69,1:03:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a participant in the event.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.40,1:03:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,People like revenge rather than forgiveness.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.40,1:03:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,They'd rather hate than forgive.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.40,1:03:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,They'd rather blame than take responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.40,1:03:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,People thrive on conflict.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.40,1:03:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,They hang into the past instead of surrendering to the present.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.43,1:04:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The fear, the basic fear is control, the basic fear.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.72,1:04:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,See, grief is hanging onto the past, the crest of the wave that has just passed.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.75,1:04:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You're clinging to that.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.75,1:04:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the past.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.75,1:04:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Fear is the anticipation of the rising crest of the wave.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.75,1:04:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So fear lives in the future.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.80,1:04:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Guilt lives in the past.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.80,1:04:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.80,1:04:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And all fears, all fears, when we get to the thing on fear, we'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.80,1:04:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,All fears eventuate as fear of physical death.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:29.93,1:04:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,All fears.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.93,1:04:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what your fear is.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.93,1:04:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And you get to that knowing this by doing the, and then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.60,1:04:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid that I won't get a raise.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.60,1:04:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.60,1:04:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.60,1:04:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I'll be broke.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.60,1:04:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.89,1:04:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:46.89,1:04:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I'll lose the job.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.89,1:04:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.89,1:04:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I'll be unemployable.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.89,1:04:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.89,1:04:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the wife will leave me.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.89,1:04:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.89,1:04:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I'll be homeless.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.01,1:04:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.01,1:04:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you'll starve to death.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.01,1:04:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.01,1:05:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If you do the, if you take every, and then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.20,1:05:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And surrender it to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.20,1:05:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so you're unemployed.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.26,1:05:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been unemployed.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.48,1:05:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll have no money.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.48,1:05:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been penniless long periods of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.48,1:05:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll be poor, penniless, and then eventually you'll die.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.50,1:05:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So you do the, and then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.14,1:05:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.14,1:05:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,If I don't get what I want, and then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.14,1:05:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I'll be disappointed.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.14,1:05:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.14,1:05:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So each, and then what, brings up a consequence.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.14,1:05:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you surrender the consequence, which is the resistance, the obstruction, you will
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.94,1:05:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,always end up with the fear of physical death.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.74,1:05:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,All fears, if you follow them through, you'll end up, and then I'll die.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.74,1:05:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Fear of physical death.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.74,1:05:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you surrender the fear of physical death to God, then the whole stack of fears collapses.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.19,1:06:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There's temerity, there's, you know, timorous, this and that.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.80,1:06:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But you're not controlled by fear.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.80,1:06:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody says, if you do so and so, you may die.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.56,1:06:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, so?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.85,1:06:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.14,1:06:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,They're trying to intimidate you with that.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.14,1:06:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.36,1:06:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You stand up for truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.36,1:06:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me kill you for that.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.36,1:06:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.88,1:06:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So once you don't have any fear of death, now you're fearless.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.88,1:06:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Fearless.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.88,1:06:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Fearless.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.97,1:06:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Fearless.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.53,1:06:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So the mind hangs on to its fears because it equates them with survival.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.56,1:06:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Because to the bacteria, to the origination of the ego's life, in the evolution of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.56,1:06:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,getting was critical and essential to life.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.63,1:06:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You had to get in order to survive.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.76,1:06:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, your ego is the same.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.76,1:06:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It thinks if I don't get blank, you just fill in the blank with what you want, then you
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.76,1:07:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,won't survive.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:01.04,1:07:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have to remind yourself I'm more than a bacteria.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.04,1:07:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,If I don't get those essential amino acids, you have to remind yourself that you are not
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.08,1:07:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,a bacteria.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.08,1:07:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.08,1:07:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Because your survival is not based on getting.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.08,1:07:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Your survival is based on your karmic inheritance and the field, the contextual field, which
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.27,1:07:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically is the consequence.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.27,1:07:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What keeps you alive is not the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.27,1:07:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What keeps you alive is the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.27,1:07:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of the spiritual field that your ego reminds you to take your vitamins.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.52,1:07:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So, your survival is not up to the linear ego, because it's only activated by the spirit.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.55,1:07:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,By the spirit.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:47.55,1:07:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of the self that you remember to take your vitamins, and you think if it
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.55,1:07:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,wasn't for the ego, I'd die of avataminosis.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.55,1:07:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.55,1:07:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.55,1:08:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the spirit.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.15,1:08:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The capital S.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.15,1:08:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The capital S is why the small S looks after you.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.47,1:08:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the big S that's your mother.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.47,1:08:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That's your mother right there, to see to it that you take your vitamins.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.47,1:08:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.79,1:08:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Survival.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.79,1:08:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So your survival is not up to the ego at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.27,1:08:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,In the middle of the desert with the truck on fire, to what did I owe my survival?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:31.33,1:08:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Mine was useless.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.33,1:08:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The intellect was useless.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.33,1:08:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no possibility of linear processing.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.33,1:08:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole situation in the physical domain, if you ever saw what the wiring looked like
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.33,1:08:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,under my old truck, it's not even discernible by an electrician.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.33,1:08:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one guy that can repair it, and I have to drive all the way down the cottonwood.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.56,1:08:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, who is the best automotive electrician around?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.56,1:09:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.56,1:09:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So even he can't figure it out.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.56,1:09:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So it wants to blame rather than take responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.90,1:09:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It thrives on conflict.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.90,1:09:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It clings to the past.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.90,1:09:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It fears the future.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.90,1:09:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It lacks excuses.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.90,1:09:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It tends to go into denial rather than to admit.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.90,1:09:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's impatient and doesn't want to wait.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.90,1:09:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Take the next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.90,1:09:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Waiting when you're uncomfortable is difficult.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.03,1:09:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So the anger of the people waiting to be rescued is the impatience.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.03,1:09:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The impatience.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.03,1:09:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The impatience.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.57,1:09:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.57,1:09:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The only way out of it is by constant surrender, constant surrender.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.96,1:09:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The locus of these things is the self.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.96,1:09:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The origin is the animal instincts.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.44,1:09:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You see impaired reality testing below consciousness level 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.66,1:09:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Intention here of the ego is to get, and the duration is transitory.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.69,1:10:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the hormonal thing here is different from adrenaline.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.08,1:10:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Emotions, passion, and attraction.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.08,1:10:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the propensity to become frantic, impaired, not be able to think right, become
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.11,1:10:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,self-destructive, to gain control.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:18.11,1:10:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, if all that collapses, to go into depression.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.59,1:10:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Depression, rage, and then hatred.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.75,1:10:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So the quality and the, you see, the attraction and the aversion.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.75,1:10:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,To forgive and choose love or resentment and getting even is difficult.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.88,1:10:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll drop, we'll go to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.88,1:10:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The quality.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:43.52,1:10:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll start.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.52,1:10:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Transcending the levels of consciousness is really written at Susan's prompting.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:51.71,1:10:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally I got into it.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:54.71,1:10:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And as I got into it, I really began to enjoy it.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:57.71,1:10:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm now extremely pleased.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:59.71,1:11:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Very, very practical.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:00.71,1:11:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to take each level.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.71,1:11:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And at the end of each chapter, there is a summary.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:07.00,1:11:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the summaries, starting with the dualities of shame.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.00,1:11:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What we talked about before are the general attractions and aversions of the ego itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.64,1:11:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we're going to talk about each level.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.64,1:11:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So in the book, we start at the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:21.64,1:11:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a chapter on each, chapter on shame, guilt, each thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.64,1:11:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And we examine each one, you know, from the viewpoint of many years in psychoanalysis
Dialogue: 0,1:11:31.64,1:11:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and psychiatry and group therapy.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.64,1:11:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Also spiritual experiences and spiritual groups.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.64,1:11:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And my own transformational experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.64,1:11:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Plus consciousness research.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.64,1:11:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So try to put together a way to approach each level from multiple angles simultaneously.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:50.80,1:11:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one sheds additional light.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:53.80,1:11:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Shame, you see, is satisfied by being self-punitive.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.52,1:12:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That's sackcloth and ashes and penance.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.62,1:12:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And the aversion is to self-forgiveness.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:04.62,1:12:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,For one thing, a person feels too guilty.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.62,1:12:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's always well to remember the admonition.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.32,1:12:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Judgment is mine, saith the Lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.32,1:12:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Judgment is mine, saith the Lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.32,1:12:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can see it's an egoistic position to assume that you're capable of making such a judgment.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.32,1:12:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The attraction is to be self-punitive.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:28.99,1:12:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The attraction of shame is depression.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.99,1:12:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd say, well, depression, people can't be attracted to that.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.99,1:12:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,They do indeed.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:37.99,1:12:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the alternate is to choose life.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.15,1:12:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The alternate is to choose life.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:43.15,1:12:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And stop hanging out in depression.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.15,1:12:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Choose life, then, is a decision.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.53,1:12:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,A decision.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.53,1:12:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what, I choose life.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.53,1:12:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The attraction here is to be judgmental against yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:58.79,1:13:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Whereas the aversion is to surrender yourself to God's mercy.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.79,1:13:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Allah the All-Merciful.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.96,1:13:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,To God the All-Merciful.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.96,1:13:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Who, of course, if He's infinite and profound,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.96,1:13:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,of course sees the weakness and frailties of the human condition.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.82,1:13:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Any good psychiatrist sees that.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:24.82,1:13:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to be God, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.82,1:13:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That the human is limited.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:28.82,1:13:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Every human is the victim of their own ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.82,1:13:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Every human is intrinsically innocent, naive,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.01,1:13:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the very nature of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.01,1:13:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The nature of the human mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.84,1:13:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We give it comparison.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.84,1:13:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The human mind is like the hardware of the computer.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:49.87,1:13:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And it'll play any software you put in it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:53.48,1:13:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You can program people and brainwash them in a matter of seconds.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.48,1:14:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what a meme is. M-E-M-E.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.48,1:14:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a catchy saying that gets picked up,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.48,1:14:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's cute, and it's in, and it's hip, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.48,1:14:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And everybody now lives by it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:07.51,1:14:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody stops to examine whether it has any truth in it or not, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:11.51,1:14:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:12.86,1:14:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the attraction is to punish yourself,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:14.86,1:14:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,hang out in depression, be judgmental,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:17.86,1:14:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than surrender judgment to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.76,1:14:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The attraction of shame is the negativity,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.76,1:14:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and the resistance is to letting go of the position.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.00,1:14:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,At all times, it is good and well to remember
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.00,1:14:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that life is a gift,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.00,1:14:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and that you are the steward of that gift.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.00,1:14:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You are the steward of that gift.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:41.32,1:14:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Steward, so.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.32,1:14:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,All gifts.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.32,1:14:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I was told that when I was young.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.45,1:14:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.58,1:14:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And I really didn't like other kids too much,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.58,1:14:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,so they took me to the psychologist.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.58,1:14:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And she said, well, he's got a very high IQ,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.61,1:14:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and he'll have to get used to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:59.61,1:15:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Just born that way.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:02.28,1:15:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Born that way.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.28,1:15:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So, here are you.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.24,1:15:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The attraction is to be negative.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.24,1:15:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't want to let go of your position.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.16,1:15:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to shrink and hide,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:14.16,1:15:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of being visible.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.84,1:15:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You see yourself as worthless,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:18.84,1:15:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,as firm, the gift of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.84,1:15:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So, whatever assets you're born with,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.84,1:15:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,so that was an asset that the priest said,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.90,1:15:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a gift from God,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:28.90,1:15:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's your responsibility
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.90,1:15:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,to utilize it for the good of mankind,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.90,1:15:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,life, others, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:36.28,1:15:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So now, instead of saying to be egoistic about,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.28,1:15:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,on the contrary,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:40.28,1:15:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,it was now a responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.54,1:15:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you have musical ability,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:45.54,1:15:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,if you have athletic ability,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.54,1:15:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,if you have good looks,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:48.54,1:15:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,if you have money with capacity
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.57,1:15:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to be really super nasty,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:53.57,1:15:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the world can use you.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.64,1:15:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That's your gift.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:56.64,1:16:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That's your gift.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:01.07,1:16:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a liar.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.58,1:16:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the best in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:04.58,1:16:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you want to hire me?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:08.69,1:16:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That was his gift, being glib.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.69,1:16:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:11.69,1:16:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.69,1:16:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you see your assets then,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:14.69,1:16:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of a source of pride or egotism,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:17.69,1:16:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of being the ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:19.69,1:16:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,now you see it's a responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.69,1:16:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Great wealth.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:22.69,1:16:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a heavy duty responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.69,1:16:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I know people of great wealth,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:27.69,1:16:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and frankly,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.69,1:16:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,their anxiety was how to best use it for mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:31.69,1:16:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,They really were concerned about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:33.69,1:16:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,They built whole empires.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:35.69,1:16:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, Rockefeller,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.69,1:16:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,all these great foundations have a huge staff of people
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.69,1:16:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,who just research the most propitious
Dialogue: 0,1:16:42.69,1:16:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and beneficial way to use this for the good of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.69,1:16:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,People don't realize that rich people can,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:48.69,1:16:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, feel a great deal of responsibility,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:51.69,1:16:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,obligation to the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:54.82,1:16:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,To see it then as a gift instead of yourself is worth,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:58.88,1:17:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, affirm that your life itself is a gift,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.88,1:17:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and how can you best use it to be of service
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.88,1:17:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to yourself and others.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.88,1:17:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it's the Dalai Lama,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.88,1:17:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,no, the skinny Indian guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.04,1:17:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Gandhi said, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.33,1:17:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Or was it the Dalai Lama?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:19.33,1:17:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:20.33,1:17:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't the skinny foreigner.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:21.33,1:17:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:26.49,1:17:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Said it is not enough, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:28.49,1:17:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to just seek enlightenment on your own
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.59,1:17:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and to pray for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:33.59,1:17:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,On the contrary,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:34.59,1:17:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,but to use whatever you can
Dialogue: 0,1:17:36.59,1:17:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,for the betterment of mankind in the meantime.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:39.59,1:17:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's Mahayana rather than Hinayana,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.59,1:17:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,in which enlightenment is for the good of all.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:47.59,1:17:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, they're the good of all.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.59,1:17:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So your enlightenment,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.59,1:17:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever talents you have,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:52.59,1:17:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,IQ, genius, good looks, strength, physicality,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.59,1:17:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the capacity for endurance,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:58.59,1:18:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and the capacity to break through barriers,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:01.59,1:18:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that's your gift.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:02.59,1:18:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And so you give thanks for the gift.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:05.59,1:18:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You're grateful.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.59,1:18:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That keeps you humble.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.59,1:18:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That way you can be rich, famous, handsome,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.59,1:18:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and good-looking like me.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.74,1:18:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Not have it go to your head.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.81,1:18:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't go to my head, does it?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:25.77,1:18:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,However you are,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:29.51,1:18:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you see the gift in it,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.51,1:18:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you are thankful and acknowledge the gift.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.51,1:18:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, thank you, God,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:36.83,1:18:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,for that disaster.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.83,1:18:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Without it,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.83,1:18:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I would never have become humble enough
Dialogue: 0,1:18:40.83,1:18:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,to realize such and such.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:42.83,1:18:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:43.83,1:18:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter what happens in life,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:44.83,1:18:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,in due time,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:45.83,1:18:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,with reflection,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.83,1:18:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,wisdom will show you
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.83,1:18:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that it was something to be thankful for.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.83,1:18:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I am thankful for every event
Dialogue: 0,1:18:53.83,1:18:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that has ever occurred in my life,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:55.83,1:18:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,although at the time,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.83,1:18:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,it was exquisite,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.83,1:18:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,painful, shameful,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.83,1:18:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,guilt-provoking,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:59.83,1:19:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,anxiety-provoking.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:00.83,1:19:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But in retrospect,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:03.95,1:19:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,you will see
Dialogue: 0,1:19:04.95,1:19:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that every experience serves.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:06.95,1:19:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of your intention
Dialogue: 0,1:19:08.95,1:19:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,to see in what way that it serves
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.95,1:19:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that it's revealed to you
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.95,1:19:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,in what way it serves.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:13.95,1:19:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,If nothing else,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.04,1:19:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,catastrophe shows
Dialogue: 0,1:19:16.04,1:19:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that your life is totally dependent on God
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.04,1:19:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and not on the human ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.04,1:19:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,because the human ego
Dialogue: 0,1:19:23.04,1:19:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,in the middle of the desert
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.04,1:19:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,with no water in the truck on foot,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.04,1:19:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,no fire,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:28.04,1:19:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is pretty powerless.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:30.04,1:19:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty powerless.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:32.04,1:19:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So, alright.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.04,1:19:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Those lessons.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:36.42,1:19:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Here the view of shame is a rigid,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.42,1:19:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't want to change it
Dialogue: 0,1:19:40.42,1:19:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and become correctable,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:41.42,1:19:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't want to accept the gift of life,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:43.42,1:19:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't want to be responsible
Dialogue: 0,1:19:45.42,1:19:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that he is now the steward of his life
Dialogue: 0,1:19:47.42,1:19:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and to stop wallowing in guilt and shame.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:50.58,1:19:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It chooses to condemn itself
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.58,1:19:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than forgive.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:53.58,1:19:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It seeks mortification
Dialogue: 0,1:19:55.58,1:19:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than affirming self-worth.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.58,1:19:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It likes to denigrate itself
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.58,1:20:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of honoring itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.58,1:20:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, once you see your life
Dialogue: 0,1:20:02.58,1:20:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,is a gift from God,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:03.58,1:20:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to honor that.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:05.58,1:20:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I honor thy presence in me, O Lord,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.93,1:20:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and I do give thanks.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:10.93,1:20:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And thereby you sanctify your life.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.93,1:20:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,When you sanctify your life,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:14.93,1:20:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you've already brought in
Dialogue: 0,1:20:15.93,1:20:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,a different spiritual context
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.93,1:20:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and your experiences of life
Dialogue: 0,1:20:19.93,1:20:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,now become confirmatory of that reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:22.93,1:20:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So instead of saying,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:24.93,1:20:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I am a worthless worm,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:28.05,1:20:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't go for wormism.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:31.05,1:20:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:32.47,1:20:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's rejecting the gift of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:38.47,1:20:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's rejecting God's gift as life.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.47,1:20:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I am a worthless worm.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.47,1:20:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you stand me, God?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.47,1:20:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's playing a game with divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:49.50,1:20:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Self-hatred instead of self-forgiveness.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.50,1:20:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,To be severe with yourself instead of benign.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:55.50,1:20:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,To be imbalanced and see both sides.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.56,1:21:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll move to the next,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.56,1:21:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'll get as far as we can
Dialogue: 0,1:21:02.43,1:21:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,within a few minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.94,1:21:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The next slide.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.94,1:21:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Next slide, please.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.10,1:21:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:12.19,1:21:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You blame yourself instead of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.19,1:21:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,To identify with the ego, you see,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.22,1:21:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you can say the mind thought that
Dialogue: 0,1:21:19.86,1:21:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,or the ego thought that,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:20.86,1:21:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,but I myself don't know
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.86,1:21:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,because the inner self is innocent.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:25.86,1:21:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of blaming the ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:29.68,1:21:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you blame the self.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.68,1:21:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You exaggerate your faults.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:32.68,1:21:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You take a partial selective view.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:34.68,1:21:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,How could I have been so stupid?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.68,1:21:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of a balanced view,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.68,1:21:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you see yourself as loser instead of corrected.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:41.68,1:21:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You saw yourself as losing
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.13,1:21:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of learning a painful lesson.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:46.13,1:21:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you lost on that one,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:48.13,1:21:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,but you're not going to bet on that one again.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:50.13,1:21:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The end of the road.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:51.39,1:21:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,This is it.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.39,1:21:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We're at the end.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:53.39,1:21:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all over.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.39,1:21:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't say that
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.61,1:21:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,loss is the beginning of the new.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:58.61,1:22:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot begin the new
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.61,1:22:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,until you let go of the old.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:02.61,1:22:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, of course,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.74,1:22:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,you see yourself unlovable,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.74,1:22:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,which is, again,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.90,1:22:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,a violation of truth
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.90,1:22:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and a negation of your worth
Dialogue: 0,1:22:09.90,1:22:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,as a child of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:11.90,1:22:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, you think the error is unforgivable.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.86,1:22:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, you see the error is a lesson.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:18.99,1:22:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Lesion.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:20.47,1:22:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that's correct, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:27.56,1:22:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a lesion.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:28.56,1:22:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a hell of an error, I tell you.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:31.62,1:22:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,This was a hell of an error, I tell you.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:36.96,1:22:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, that's good.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:37.96,1:22:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Lesion.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.96,1:22:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.28,1:22:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody can spell it correctly.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.28,1:22:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:42.28,1:22:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Narcissistic concern.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:43.48,1:22:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, you're concerned for others.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:44.48,1:22:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.48,1:22:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, help me, help me,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.48,1:22:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,it's how can I help you?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:47.48,1:22:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And by helping them,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.48,1:22:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you're the one that gets saved.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:49.48,1:22:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Indulgence.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.48,1:22:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of letting go,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.48,1:22:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,self is the center of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:52.48,1:22:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Self is a participant in life.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.48,1:22:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Focus on the self instead of others.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:54.70,1:22:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I should have done this.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.70,1:22:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And the reality is,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:56.70,1:22:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,you are not.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:57.70,1:22:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You are not.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.70,1:22:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You are not.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.70,1:23:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You are not.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:00.70,1:23:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You are not.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:02.02,1:23:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You are not.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.02,1:23:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You are not.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.02,1:23:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You are not.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:05.02,1:23:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You are not.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.02,1:23:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You are not.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:07.02,1:23:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You are not.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.02,1:23:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You are not able to.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.02,1:23:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go to the next slide.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:11.85,1:23:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I should have this or should have that is dealing from the hypothetical.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.85,1:23:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The hypothetical is always wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:16.85,1:23:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Any time you hear your mind saying,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.85,1:23:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,you should have or ought to have,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:20.85,1:23:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,negate it.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:21.85,1:23:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,There isn't such a thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:22.85,1:23:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,If you could have,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:23.95,1:23:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,you would have.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.95,1:23:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that you didn't is because you couldn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.01,1:23:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,There you see,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.01,1:23:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,at the time,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.01,1:23:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a sore in my foot.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:32.08,1:23:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't run any faster.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:36.08,1:23:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,If you could have run faster,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.08,1:23:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you would have, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:39.08,1:23:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.33,1:23:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Guilt and shame then,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:42.88,1:23:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,guilt and hate go together
Dialogue: 0,1:23:45.88,1:23:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's judgmental
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.88,1:23:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and you end up punishing either you
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.91,1:23:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,or projecting it outwards.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.91,1:23:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the refusal of mercy
Dialogue: 0,1:23:54.91,1:23:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and the secret pleasure of guilt.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:59.26,1:24:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,See, self-punishment is a secret,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:01.26,1:24:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,is a secret pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:03.26,1:24:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you project your feelings
Dialogue: 0,1:24:06.38,1:24:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of taking responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.38,1:24:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you choose perception
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.38,1:24:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and with the spirit you choose to see the essence.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:16.04,1:24:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Guilt and hate is due to a rigid narrow view
Dialogue: 0,1:24:19.04,1:24:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of seeing both sides.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.04,1:24:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You're walking in your brother's moccasins,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:24.04,1:24:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,then you can see
Dialogue: 0,1:24:26.04,1:24:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,what it would be like to walk in his moccasins.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.43,1:24:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you see penance and self-indulgence as attractive
Dialogue: 0,1:24:33.43,1:24:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of being of service to others.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:36.56,1:24:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What good does it do others
Dialogue: 0,1:24:38.56,1:24:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to say the rosary all morning?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:40.56,1:24:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me that.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:41.56,1:24:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.07,1:24:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Other than you get sore knuckles.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.07,1:24:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But how did you help the world?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:48.07,1:24:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Of what service were you?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:50.07,1:24:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:51.07,1:24:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You cling to your position
Dialogue: 0,1:24:52.07,1:24:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of asking God for a miracle.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.07,1:24:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you have a willingness to change.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:57.39,1:25:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Here there's this attraction to act out
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.39,1:25:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of transcending.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.39,1:25:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And here people enjoy,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.42,1:25:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,in guilt and hate people enjoy being mean.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.42,1:25:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And here they enjoy being gracious and selfless,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:10.42,1:25:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to be small and mean
Dialogue: 0,1:25:12.42,1:25:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,with yourself or others.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.42,1:25:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, it's being small and mean with yourself,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.42,1:25:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.42,1:25:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,which is a denial of
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.42,1:25:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the divinity of life within you,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.42,1:25:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,your soul, your being,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.61,1:25:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and loving towards divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.61,1:25:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the next one that we're not going to get to do?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.96,1:25:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Guilt and hate, is that more of it?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.24,1:25:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Hate?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.24,1:25:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, we'll do it quickly and then we'll stop.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.24,1:25:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I won't have to feel guilty that I didn't finish it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:47.48,1:25:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to be right rather than be wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.48,1:25:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You see yourself as hopeless
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.48,1:25:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of flexible,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:54.48,1:25:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.48,1:26:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of transcending it, you wallow in it.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.21,1:26:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Guilt and hate can lead to very malignant and cruel behavior
Dialogue: 0,1:26:04.21,1:26:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of being benign and merciful.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:06.50,1:26:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:07.50,1:26:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's stingy instead of generous.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:10.92,1:26:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It projects responsibility
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.92,1:26:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of choosing to be the author.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:16.27,1:26:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Guilt and hate are very vengeful,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:18.27,1:26:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,comes from smallness, very grasping,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.27,1:26:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's the refusal to be
Dialogue: 0,1:26:24.30,1:26:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,benevolent and merciful
Dialogue: 0,1:26:26.30,1:26:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and choose to be bigger than that.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:28.33,1:26:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:30.00,1:26:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.00,1:26:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So we stop there for today because
Dialogue: 0,1:26:34.29,1:26:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,as I said, I'd feel guilty if I didn't get past that one.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.29,1:26:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd be ashamed of myself,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:40.29,1:26:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,have to attack myself and get depressed.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.66,1:26:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:46.88,1:26:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So what happens next now?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.88,1:26:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Three o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:49.88,1:26:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to have...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.88,1:26:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:52.24,1:26:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Nico's going to chant.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:54.24,1:26:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody relax.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.60,1:27:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Let your chair support you
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.56,1:27:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and pretend it's the whole universe, okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:05.59,1:27:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Buddha said,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.76,1:27:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,sit upright and chant this sutra.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:19.88,1:27:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And a common moral says,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:23.86,1:27:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,time without beginning,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:25.89,1:27:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,but instead chant this sutra
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.36,1:27:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,for profound realization
Dialogue: 0,1:27:33.03,1:27:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that this last moment
Dialogue: 0,1:27:36.53,1:27:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,is the beginning.
